    "updated_at": "2024-09-27T09:46:01Z",
    "body": "I have encountered the same issue on another platform.\r\n\r\nI'm using PowerShell in Windows Terminal, and when I use the '[Clear buffer](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/terminal/customize-settings/actions#clear-buffer)' command provided by Windows Terminal, the first line of the prompt also disappears.\r\n\r\nnormal:\r\n<img src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/77e984e2-261e-441d-89ec-d1c08984ad54\" width=\"600\">\r\n\r\nafter 'Clear buffer':\r\n<img src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0edeef55-550c-4321-8dc6-e4af15d89032\" width=\"600\">\r\n\r\nwhen I type something, the cursor jumps to the third line, as if the prompt is still in its normal position.\r\n<img src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/eeb5bf2f-b7c7-47b5-8e42-2cd2b68efbbf\" width=\"600\">\r\n\r\n### Environment\r\nStarship version: 1.20.1\r\nShell: PowerShell 5.1.22621.4111\r\nTerminal emulator: Windows Terminal 1.20.11781.0\r\nOperating system: Windows 11 Home 23H2\r\n\r\n### Starship Configuration\r\n```toml\r\n[character]\r\nsuccess_symbol = '[~>](bold green)'\r\nerror_symbol = '[✗](bold red)'\r\n```\r\n",
